<strong>WORKS CITED</strong>
<br><br>
Add a &#8216;Works Cited&#8217; entry at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br><br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	Author&#8217;s name. <em>Title of Book</em>. Publisher, year of publication.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br><br>
	If the publisher is an academic press, replace <em>University</em> with <em>U</em>. For further information on publisher abbreviations, see 1.6.3 in the <a href="https://west-sydney-primo.hosted.exlibrisgroup.com/UWS-ALMA:default_scope:UWS-ALMA21186157620001571" target="_blank" title="opens a new window">MLA Handbook (8th edition)</a>. 
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Author&#8217;s name">Smith, Anu R.</span> 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Book">Teaching and Learning in Higher Education</span></em>.
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">U Books</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="year of publication">2056</span>. 
</blockquote>
